---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Paraguay Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/paraguay/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Argentina for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/argentina' },
  { title: 'Uruguay for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uruguay' },
  { title: 'Brazil for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/brazil' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'paraguayFit', header: 'Paraguay Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PYG$2.2M-3.1M/mo', paraguayFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PYG$2.6M-3.7M/mo', paraguayFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PYG$2.0M-2.8M/mo', paraguayFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PYG$1.8M-2.6M/mo', paraguayFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Asismed, Medical)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'PYG$800K-1.5M/mo', paraguayFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'PYG$2.0M-3.1M', annual: 'PYG$24M-37M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'PYG$2.7M-4.2M', annual: 'PYG$33M-50M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'PYG$3.7M-5.6M', annual: 'PYG$44M-68M' },
  { category: 'Local Private Insurance', monthly: 'PYG$800K-1.5M/mo', annual: 'PYG$9.6M-18M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'PYG$1.5M-4M/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Paraguay 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Paraguay. Affordable living, easy residency, low taxes, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Paraguay"
  subheadline="Paraguay offers exceptionally affordable living, easy residency process, low taxes, and friendly people—South America's hidden gem for budget-conscious retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/paraguay-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Paraguay</h2>
  <p>
    Paraguay offers extremely affordable living, one of the easiest residency processes in the world, territorial tax system (foreign income not taxed), and genuine hospitality. For budget-conscious retirees willing to go off the beaten path, Paraguay provides remarkable value.
  </p>

  <p>
    Asunción is the capital with best healthcare and infrastructure. Ciudad del Este offers commercial hub near Iguazu Falls. Encarnación on Paraná River has colonial charm. Mennonite colonies in Chaco offer German community. Most expats choose Asunción area for services.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving in Asunción; limited elsewhere</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish; Guaraní</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> PYG$5M-10M/month (~$650-1,300 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Subtropical; hot summers; mild winters</li>
      <li><strong>Taxes:</strong> Territorial; foreign income not taxed</li>
      <li><strong>Residency:</strong> Among easiest in world</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Paraguay Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Paraguay healthcare is improving—private hospitals in Asunción provide decent quality. Hospital Italiano, Hospital Privado del Norte, and Sanatorio Migone are leading facilities. Quality varies; complex cases may require Buenos Aires or São Paulo (both 1-2 hours by air).
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is limited. Private care is affordable but variable quality. Asunción has best options; rural healthcare is basic. Buenos Aires provides nearby backup for complex conditions. International insurance with regional coverage recommended.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Regional Backup</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Paraguay healthcare handles routine care; complex conditions may need Buenos Aires or São Paulo. Both are short flights away. Ensure insurance covers regional evacuation. Private hospitals in Asunción are improving but have limitations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Paraguay has remarkably easy residency:
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residency</h3>
  <p>
    Among easiest in world—income requirement only ~$1,500/month or bank deposit. Process takes weeks not years. Direct path to permanent residency for most applicants.
  </p>

  <h3>Retiree/Rentista Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with pension income. Very low threshold (~$1,000-1,500/month). Straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing $70,000+ in Paraguay. Leads to permanent residency quickly.
  </p>

  <h3>Citizenship</h3>
  <p>
    After 3 years of residency, can apply for citizenship. Paraguay allows dual citizenship.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Paraguay:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residency:</strong> Health insurance generally required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> Include Argentina/Brazil coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Local option:</strong> Affordable but limited networks</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Paraguay</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with regional coverage recommended. Include Buenos Aires and São Paulo for complex conditions. Local insurance affordable but networks limited. High deductible plans work well with affordable local care for routine needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Paraguay, regional coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Paraguay</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Americas coverage, strong regional network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Local (Asismed):</strong> Paraguay network but age limits</li>
    <li><strong>Buenos Aires access:</strong> Critical for complex care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with regional South America access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Paraguay (PYG ~7,700 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable; save on premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Self-pay routine:</strong> Doctor visits very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Asunción base:</strong> Best healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>Regional network:</strong> Use Buenos Aires for complex care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Budget Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month Social Security. Permanent residency. Asunción.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with high deductible. Self-pay routine care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~PYG$2.4M/month (~$310). Stretch pension far; Buenos Aires backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: German Expat, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,000/month pension. Investor residency. Mennonite colony.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with worldwide. German community support.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~PYG$3.2M/month (~$415). European backup; community living.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Brazilian Neighbor, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> R$8,000/month income. Easy residency. Ciudad del Este.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Brazil coverage. São Paulo backup.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~PYG$2.1M/month (~$275). Cross-border life; Brazilian healthcare option.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Paraguay really that cheap?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—among South America's most affordable countries. $1,000-1,500/month covers comfortable living. Rent $300-500 for nice apartment. Meals $3-10. Healthcare very affordable. Genuine value destination for those on tight budget.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is residency really that easy?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Paraguay has one of world's easiest residency processes. Income requirement ~$1,500/month or bank deposit. Process takes weeks. Many facilitators help navigate. Direct path to permanent residency and citizenship.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Spanish?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Spanish essential in Paraguay. Guaraní also widely spoken. English very limited outside international business. Learning Spanish important for daily life. Expat community smaller than neighboring countries.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Paraguay safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—lower crime than neighbors. Asunción has typical urban issues. Rural areas quiet. Border areas (Ciudad del Este) have some smuggling concerns. Common sense precautions apply. Overall safe for expats.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Paraguay coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Paraguay authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
